misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes a right-rotation by 1 can be done by saving the last element, shifting elements right from the end toward index 1, then writing the saved last element into index 0.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No conceptual gap detected. This matches Java’s actual array update behavior (in-place mutation) and correctly avoids overwriting needed values by iterating from right to left.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No error; produces the required shifted output (including correct wrap-around). Handles N=0 safely by skipping the shift.
